The Director-General of the Plateau State Contributory Health Care Management Agency (PLASCHEMA), Dr Fabong Yildam, says the agency has engaged the Association of Community Pharmacists in making available drugs for the agency’s clients. Yildam said this on Tuesday in Jos during a forum organised by the Correspondents’ Chapel, Nigeria Union of Journalists (NUJ) in Plateau. He noted that the agency had also included the management of snakebites under its healthcare insurance coverage. (NAN)